race.description: Tassie Fine Foods Pb Ronald Handicap (Bm78)
race.comment: JENNI GONE BONKERS (9) has to go on top. Her 2yo form last time in was excellent, resuming with a dominant maiden win in fast time which saw her backed off the map to start $1.55 in the Listed Twilight Glow at Caulfield last time. She tried hard there and the winner ran out on her slightly which couldn't have helped. Takes on the older horses here but they look to have hit their mark and getting to a mile should suit nicely now. ASTRAL FLAME (2) is the danger. Forgive the flop on heavy ground two back, she was better in the Rising Stars Class 3 at Cranbourne last time when working home to just miss. Don't think a mile will be a problem. I ONLY WISH (8) comes back slightly in trip off a good run at Flemington and will be the one staying on strongly if they go hard enough. MISS PLAYLOUNGE (6) has minor claims off a win in easier while DRAW ATTENTION (10) was close up in the ASTRAL FLAME race fresh at big odds and has to be respected.
